<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — The body is supposed to sit near the <strong>bottom</strong>, where the player ship belongs. Right now it is drawn near the top of the screen.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">pygame.draw.rect(screen, CYAN, (CENTER_X - 20, 80, 40, 50))
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> in Pygame, Y = 0 is the <strong>top</strong>. The bottom is near <code>HEIGHT</code>.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
